recent_articles.title: Coca-Cola says it appreciates Trump's 'enthusiasm' after president says company will use real sugar in drinks
Trump & Coca-Cola, Novartis earnings, Netflix preview: Trending Tickers
recent_articles.summary:
President Trump says Coca-Cola (KO) will switch to real cane sugar in US drinks, though the company has yet to confirm, pressuring corn futures and shares of companies that make corn syrup including ADM (ADM) and Ingredion (INGR).

Novartis (NVS) reported a second quarter earnings beat and announced a $10 billion buyback. The company also revealed its CFO is retiring, and sales of a key drug disappointed.

Netflix (NFLX) reports earnings after the bell, with strong revenue and profit growth expected as investors weigh high expectations and valuation.
